Why I write about it now?
Gotta honor him somehow
Saw some people crying that night
Yeah, Fentanyl took a few lives from our life
Alright

songs.name: Can't Get It Out
songs.lyrics:
As we glide over whatever
We know to be over forever
I really hope the shame is less
For what we feel in times of stress

No sense in fighting it now
You had me caught in your headlights
You were running me down

We speak in tongues and start to teethe
Lift your voice and scrape your knees
Kids in love will plant a seed
Resurrect and start to breathe

songs.name: Gone For Good
songs.lyrics:
Making that mistake was a serious task
How can I hear your voice again
My only concern wasn't making it last
Somehow I cut it off short

She was holding back, never wanting change
She never thought she could
Then she realized when he finally left
Maybe he was gone for good
Gone for good

Everything I wanted ended up in the fire
How am I in the same place

songs.name: Stairwell Song
songs.album: Down in the Weeds, Where the World Once Was
songs.lyrics:
Underneath, an awning
Concentrating on the rain
Hearing laughter in the stairwell
It reverberates
They talkin 'bout the weekend
All the plans that they have made
Said it's just nice to have something
To anticipate

We were dressed alike
Though you were one of a kind
For an enigmatic guy
You seemed relatable

You were smart
But so foolish with your heart
Eyed the exit from the start
